	abstract = {Today, blockchain is given attention in tourism, and research has begun about it. This study aimed to present a business model on blockchain platform. Blockchain is a shared distributed ledger that can lead to secure transactions in the tourism industry through a secure network. This research adopted a qualitative approach and relied upon the thematic analysis method. Data analysis showed that blockchain platform changes business models in tourism. That is to say the customer sector includes peer-to-peer exchanges and smart contracts, product and service sections include primary and secondary values, infrastructure management includes infrastructure as well as physical and human resources, the financial sector for revenues includes mining and earning national and international revenues and for costs includes the costs of setting up the platform on a blockchain platform, supporting and bringing about specialized development of the platform, and purchasing of a minor.},
